# RunMapper

RunMapper is an iPad-first Progressive Web App for **planning and saving running routes as GPX files**. The user taps points on a map, RunMapper snaps the segments to real footpaths/roads via [BRouter](https://brouter.de/brouter-web/), and the result can be exported to a `.gpx` file or stored in a local library.

## Primary user

A runner planning a route on an iPad before going out. Must work in Safari (PWA installable to home screen).

## Core capabilities (v1)

- Map-based waypoint editor (tap to add, drag to move, tap-on-line to insert, tap-marker to select/delete).
- Per-leg navigation routing through BRouter (profiles: `trekking`, `fastbike`, `hiking-mountain`, `shortest`).
- Distance, ascent, descent stats and an SVG elevation profile.
- Open / Save / Save As `.gpx` — File System Access API on Chromium, download/upload fallback on iPad Safari.
- Local IndexedDB-backed library (list / load / rename / delete saved routes).
- Undo / redo with snapshot-based history.
- Installable PWA with offline-cached map tiles and routing responses.

## Explicit non-goals (do NOT build without an explicit ask)

- Cloud accounts, sync, or any backend.
- Strava / Komoot import or export.
- Live GPS recording during a run.
- Turn-by-turn voice navigation.
- A second profile family beyond BRouter's built-ins.

These were ruled out for v1 to keep the app a static SPA with no backend. Adding any of them requires a new design pass.
